@node Introduction "Short introduction about De-Archiveur"

@{b}Introduction about De-Archiveur @{ub}

De-Archiveur  is  a  Graphical  User  Interface that allows to control
archivers like LHA, LZH, LZX, ZIP,DMS,UNARJ,UNRAR.

De-Archiveur  can  extract  a  archive that mean you can add,substract
decrunch,  delete  one or more files and also read, see or play a file
with your usual programs.

De-Archiveur can convert an archive in LHA, LZX or ZIP with an original
in LHA,LZH,LZX,ZIP,UNARJ,UNRAR.

De-Archiveur  is  a  specialy developped program that enable, even the
novice, user to pack, unpack program or extract, convert archive using
most  of  the  various  archivers  around,  without  needing  to learn
multitude of commands.

@endnode

@Node systemerequis "What do you need to launch De-Archiveur"

@{b}Necessary system for De-Archiveur@{ub}

De-Archiveur  is  a  program  written  in BlitzBasic that use specific
instructions  of  the  kickstart  3.0.   De-Archiveur  work  only with
Kickstart 3.0 or superior.

This  program  use the brilliant Reqtools.library by Nico François and
Magnus Holmgren in your drawer @{b}LIBS:@{ub} of your system.

The installer is necessary for using the install script.

This  program  was written in a A1200 with 030/42 and 8mb and a A1200 with
030/50  and  16  mb of fast.  This program work in different configuration
such as:

-A1500T+PICASSO4 with Picasso96+Video Option (PAL)+BlizzardIV+22MB Fast.

@EndNode

