@Node Utilisation "First Use"
@{b}For a good start@{ub}

The  first  time,  it's  necessary  to configure De-Archiveur with the
Workbench  menu icon->information for the fonts to use, Where you want
the  place  of  the  Appicon  of  De-Archiveur,  the coordinate of the
window, the hotkey and popkey, ....and the normal path of your usual
programs with the @{" Preferences globales " LINK preference3} of De-Archiveur
or when you use De-Archiveur for the first time.

After, launch it whith double-clicking in his icon.  A window with all
the  possibility of De-Archiveur appared.  You MUST configure the path
of each archiveurs you have, the drawer for the documentations....

You  can  iconify De-Archiveur with the gadget in the left high of the
principal window.  Double-click in the Appicon show you again the GUI.

De-Archiveur is a commodity and is completely checked with Exchange or
similar  clone  of  the  workbench  (like CX).  Exchange allows you to
switch off, quitting, show GUI of De-Archiveur, etc....

In an Appicon form, De-Archiveur allows you to pack or unpack directly
with  dropping  the  archive or the drawer you want and enter the name
you want with the prefix of the archiver you neeed.
@Endnode

@Node Fenetre principale "The principal window"

@{b}The principal window of De-Archiveur@{ub}

@{" Menu  " LINK Menu} 

                  Blitz De-Archiveur

             @{"  AUTO    " LINK FENETRE1}     @{" SETTINGS " LINK FENETRE1}
             @{"  UNPACK  " LINK FENETRE1}     @{"   PACK   " LINK FENETRE1}
             @{"  EXTRACT " LINK FENETRE1}     @{" CONVERT  " LINK FENETRE1}
             @{"  TEST    " LINK FENETRE1}     @{"   ABOUT  " LINK FENETRE1}

		@{" QUIT " LINK QUITTER}
             
@Endnode

@Node FENETRE1

AUTO:

Allow  De-Archiveur  to  choose  atomatically the archiver you need or
select the archivers you use the most often.

SETTINGS:

Give an access to the config window of De-Archiveur.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + S

UNPACK:

Unpack  one  or  more  file  with  a file-requester in the drawer you have
choosen   in  the  prefs  window.   If  the  box  'Valid  requester  -path
destination'  is  choosen,  you  can  choose  the  target  you want before
unpacking.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + U

PACK:

Pack  one  or more file and before De-Archiveur ask you which name it must
use  for the archive (a default name is also possible).  If the box 'Valid
requester  -  path  destination' is choosen, you can choose the target you
want before packing.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + P

EXTRACT:

After loading an archive, all the files appared in a window. Some gadgets
at the buttom of the window allows you to crunch or decrunch or add, delete
one or more files and also read, listen or see one or more files.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + F

CONVERT:

Convert an archive LHA,LZH,LZX,ZIP,UNARJ,UNRAR in LHA,LZX or ZIP.

keyboard shortcut:  AMIGA + C

TEST:

Test the integrity of an archive.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + T

ABOUT:

The  about  requester show you informations about De-Archiveur and his
authors.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + A

QUIT:

Quit De-Archiveur

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + Q

@Endnode

@node Menu "Menus of the principal window"

All the options of the principal window are also in the menu with:

ICONIFY:

This option and the gadget at the high left of the principal window
give you the possibility to iconify the program. After, you can directly
put the icon of the archive and a requester gave you different choice.

DOC:

This  documentation  is  available  directly  in De-Archiveur.  Simply
click  in  the  doc  button  and  have the good path of the Amigaguide
Documentation in the pref.

keyboard shortcut:  AMIGA + D

SETTINGS:

Show you the @{" Program settings " LINK preference1}

SETTINGS CONVERT:

Show you the @{" convert settings " LINK preference2} 

GLOBAL SETTINGS:

Show you the @{" global settings " LINK preference3} 

@Endnode 

;-------------------------

@Node extraction "Fenetre d'extraction"

- In the high of the window: The name of the loaded archive.
- Below : All the files for the loaded archive.

An arrow show you the files you have specially selected by cliquing in
his name. A second selection cancelled the precedent choice. 

- In the low : A list of buttons:

@{" Extract file(s)   " LINK FENETRE2} @{" Add file(s)      " LINK FENETRE2}
@{" Delete file(s)    " LINK FENETRE2} @{" Read a file      " LINK FENETRE2}
@{" Play a  module    " LINK FENETRE2} @{" View picture     " LINK FENETRE2}

@{"   Load            " LINK FENETRE2} @{"    Cancel    " LINK FENETRE2}

@Endnode

@Node fenetre2

EXTRACT-FILE(S):

Crunch one or mores files in the loaded archive.

ADD-FILE(S):

Add a file in the loaded archive.

DELETE-FILE(S):

Delete a file in the loaded archive.

READ A FILE:

After using the setting file, you can see a text file with your prefered
text viewers.

PLAY A MODULE:

After using the setting file, you can play a module with your prefered
player of modules.

VIEW PICTURE:

After using the setting file, you can see pictures with your prefered
picture viewers.

LOAD:

Load an archive.

CANCEL:

Back to the main window.
@Endnode 
;------------
@Node convertion "Fenetre de convertion"

Somes options are available:

@{" Select archive    " LINK FENETRE3}
@{" Select packer     " LINK FENETRE3}
@{" Tempory drawer    " LINK FENETRE3}
@{" Settings          " LINK FENETRE3}
@{"     OK            " LINK FENETRE3} @{"   Cancel    " LINK FENETRE3}

@Endnode

@Node fenetre3

SELECT ARCHIVE:

Choose an archive to convert.

SELECT PACKER:

Choose to packer you want to use (LHA,LZX,ZIP).

TEMPORY DRAWER:

The working drawer ( Default: Ram:T ).

CONVERT SETTINGS:

Give you an access to the @{" settings convert " LINK preference2} 

OK:

Lauch the conversion.

CANCEL:

Go back to the main menu.

@Endnode 
;-------------------------------------------
@Node Preference1 "Program preferences"

@{b} Preferences window  @{ub}

	     @{" Settings archiveurs " LINK FENETRE4}

	@{" Path Source      " LINK FENETRE4}   @{" Cmd unpacker " LINK FENETRE4}
	@{" Path Destination " LINK FENETRE4}   @{" Cmd packer   " LINK FENETRE4}
	@{" Use packer       " LINK FENETRE4}   @{" Cmd test     " LINK FENETRE4}
	@{" Use unpacker     " LINK FENETRE4}   @{" Cmd shell    " LINK FENETRE4}
	@{" DMS Method       " LINK FENETRE4}   @{" close shell  " LINK FENETRE4}

			@{"  Path destination  " LINK FENETRE4} 

        @{" Save settings " LINK FENETRE4}   @{" Use " LINK FENETRE4}    @{" Quit " LINK FENETRE4}

Explanations for each options are the same for all the archivers.

Keyboard shortcup: AMIGA + S

@endnode

@Node fenetre4

SETTINGS:

With  this  button,  you  can  choose  the archiver you want to change
parameters available with De-Archiver.

PATH SOURCE:

The path you habitually use where your archived programs are stocking.

CMD-PACKER:

Commands necessary for packing an archive.   

PATH DESTINATION:

The path you habitually use to stocking your archived programs.

CMD UNPACKER:

Commands necessary for unpacking an archive.

USE PACKER:

The path where your packers are.

CMD-TEST:

Commands necessary for testing or listing an archive.

USE UNPACKER:

The path where your unpackers are (for example unzip).

CMD-SHELL:

Commands necessary for creating a shell window.

ex: Newcli window con:0/11/640/100/De-Archiveur/close.

CLOSE SHELL:

You  can  choose  the time you want to see the shell window containing
the   informations  of  the  archive  after  a  packing  or  unpacking
operation.

It's impossible to quit the window before the time.

Don't put a too long time.

DMS METHOD:

You can choose the method you want to use DMS.

PATH DESTINATION:

You can have a requester for choosing a particular destination with this
option or often the same destination when using the general settings.
(Default:RAM)

SAVE SETTINGS:

Save settings.

USE:

Only use the new settings.

QUIT:

Quit the program.

@EndNode
;--------------------------------
@Node preference2 "Convert Settings"

4 buttons in the settings convert:

@{"  Method  LZX      " LINK FENETRE5}   @{"  Save settings   " LINK FENETRE5}
@{"  Delete archive   " LINK FENETRE5}   @{"  Use             " LINK FENETRE5}

keyboard shortcut:  AMIGA + C 

@EndNode

@Node fenetre5

METHOD LZX:

Choose the efficiency you want when using LZX to convert an archive.
(Default: -2 ).  4 possibility are available:

(-1): Fast
(-2): Defaut
(-3): More
(-9): Best. Only with the registered version of LZX.

SAVE SETTINGS:

Save all the settings of De-Archiveur.

DELETE ORIGINAL ARCHIVE:

Allow you to choose if you want to keep the original archive after
converting it with a new packer.

USE:

Use the settings untill you quit the program.

@EndNode

